     "You are not hearing the wind — you are hearing the LEAVES. Rustle is a dense stochastic micro-transient texture, so the spectral tilt INVERTS relative to every other wind: high_band_energy ~0.52 and spectral_centroid_hz ~3.4 kHz, against low_band_energy ~0.42 and ~900 Hz for WIND-GENERAL. onset_rate_per_second is high (~22/s) while onset_periodicity stays near zero: dense, but not rhythmic.",
